The paper proposes a novel graph auto-encoder framework for attributed network embedding, which involves learning low-dimensional node representations from both network structure and node attributes. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically, representation learning. The paper also involves network analysis and modeling (cs.SI), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with link prediction and node classification tasks. Finally, the paper uses real-world datasets to evaluate the proposed framework, which falls under the category of software development (cs.SD).
